originalText.text: I worked with Ms. DiPietro on several cases while I was a law clerk to a New York State Supreme Court judge handling guardianship matters. We appointed her as an attorney for allegedly incapacitated persons and as a guardian for people both with and without significant estates. Ms. DiPietro always performed her duties in an exemplary manner and for the best interests of her clients. In one especially difficult case she was able to rectify mistakes made by a previous attorney. I can highly recommend Sylvia DiPietro as a trust and estates attorney and as a guardian.
